title: Religious Music Of The Middle Ages
description:
More than a hundred downloads the first 24 hours for my last torrent, so here&#039;s  another. In keeping with my general policy, I will only be including half the available tracks on any given album, and encourage you to fill in the gaps by supporting the artists and purchasing the CD&#039;s. Even so, this is a healthy dollop of period music!

This is all new material -- it is not included in any of my other medieval/hymnal  torrents. A good portion of Middle Eastern Christian music is included. In order, they are:

A Star In The East (Anonymous 4)
Chants Byzantin (Sister Mary Keyrouz)
Chants Chretiens Arameens (Esther Lamandier)
An English Ladymass (Anonymous 4)
Hildegard von Bingen und ihre Zeit (Music fur fruhe Musik Augsberg)
Lutheran Mass For Christmas Morning (Gabrielle Consort & Players)
Medieval Christmas (Boston Camerata)
Psallite!- A Renaissance Christmas (Boston Camerata)
Sing We Noel (Boston Camerata)
The Ancient Miracles (Music fur fruhe Musik Augsberg)
Vision (Richard Souther/Hildegard von Bingen) 

All are high quality rips at 320 bps. Enjoy, and feel free to download my other torrents if you enjoy this fine old music -- and keep seeding!
